<property name="userLevelDocumentation" class="ptolemy.kernel.util.ConfigurableAttribute"><configure><p>The ArrayMaximum actor reads an array of elements (e.g., {3,12,33,2,4}) and outputs the value and the index of the largest element via its output and index ports, respectively. If the array contains more than one element with the maximum value, the actor outputs the index of the first occurrence of the value.</p>

<p>The first element in an array has an index of 0, the second element has an index of 1, the third has an index of 2, etc.</p></configure></property>
<property name="port:output" class="ptolemy.kernel.util.ConfigurableAttribute"><configure>An output port that broadcasts the value of the largest array element.</configure></property>
<property name="port:input" class="ptolemy.kernel.util.ConfigurableAttribute"><configure>An input port that accepts an array of elements (e.g., {1,2,3,4,5}).</configure></property>
<property name="port:index" class="ptolemy.kernel.util.ConfigurableAttribute"><configure>An output port that broadcasts the index of the largest array element. For example, if the input array is {1,2,3,4,5}, the port will output 4, which is the index of the largest value in the array. Note that the first element in an array has an index of 0.</configure></property>
</property>
